description:
Open The Door, Earthman!

A man is wandering through the woods when he encounters two aliens. The aliens are standing before two scarlet boxes. One box is completely empty. The other holds a death ray. The aliens issue an ultimatum to the man. Open the right box, and the Earth will be spared an invasion. Open the wrong box, and the aliens will conquer the world. The man is given five minutes to make his decision. The man frantically attempts to determine which box is the empty one. He taps on them, but they both sound hollow. He lifts them, but they both weigh the same. He moves towards each box, as if to open it, to gage the aliens' reaction, but their expressions never change. With the clock running down, the man finally selects the box on the right. It is empty. Taking the aliens' words literally has solved the riddle. The aliens depart to play their horrendous "game" on some other world.
name: Dangerous Journey To Earth

description:
The Man With Future-Vision!

Robert Morton, a caretaker at Allied Sciences Research Laboratories, foolishly presses a button, in the cosmic ray chamber. Morton's eyes are hit by cosmic rays. Morton is quick to discover that he can no longer perceive the world as it is in the present. Morton, instead, sees the world as it will be three months in the future. Posing as a blind man to protect himself from present dangers he cannot perceive, Morton goes about recording data that will make him a wealthy man. Morton sees a doctor, to restore his normal vision. Returning home, Morton is horrified to discover that the vase he secreted his data inside, didn't exist in the present. In reality, he actually just dropped the information on the floor. Morton's cleaning lady, assuming the papers to be trash, incinerated them,
name: The Man With Future-Vision!

Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Hunted Big Game in Outer Space!
  • I Found Davey Jones' Locker!
  • I Was Lost in a Mirage!

The issue also features the following small comic strips:

  • Binky's Special Election Exhibit
  • Moolah the Mystic

I Hunted Big Game in Outer Space

When a group of three big game hunters make a wish that they could hunt dinosaurs a strange man grants their wish, taking them to a foreign planet to grant them their desires. Are these hunters up for the challenge or has mankind lost its spot within the food chain?

I Found Davey Jones' Locker

The mythical figure known as Davey Jones haunts all those who sail through harsh conditions; however, his treasure awaits those who are brave enough to face the challenge. When two sailors locate the treasure they decide to make a go for it, but will they lose their lives in the process?

I Was Lost in a Mirage

When Clint, a pilot, crash lands in the Sahara he enters a mysterious world, but is what he's seeing actually there or is it all some sort of mirage?

Binky's Special Election Exhibit

Binky explains the importance of voting to the readers.

Moolah the Mystic

Is Moolah a fortune teller or a bowler? Maybe he's both!
name: I Was Lost in a Mirage
